{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775851191089,"sessionID":"ses_2870582ffffef45IGbHMxX3FsL","part":{"id":"prt_d78fab775001JmJoBW9ZfMItZC","messageID":"msg_d78faacb30017B2dgR2RtFZB34","sessionID":"ses_2870582ffffef45IGbHMxX3FsL","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_54a831dc3ef743c5a3986aef","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: AR-012 — 会话存储接口定义\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Define and implement a `Store` interface in `pkg/store` for persisting sandbox metadata keyed by session ID, with Redis and Valkey backend support. The interface supports session CRUD operations, expiry and last-activity indexing for garbage collection, and provider selection via configuration.\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: ### Background\n10: \n11: The agentcube system requires persistent storage for sandbox metadata associated with user sessions. Currently, there is no standardized interface for session storage, making it difficult to:\n12: - Support different storage backends (Redis, Valkey)\n13: - Index sessions for garbage collection (expired/inactive sessions)\n14: - Maintain session metadata independently of the runtime lifecycle\n15: \n16: ### Goal\n17: \n18: Implement a `Store` interface with:\n19: - Unified API for session CRUD operations\n20: - Support for Redis and Valkey backends\n21: - Indexed queries for expired and inactive sessions\n22: - Singleton access pattern for application-wide storage\n23: \n24: ### Value\n25: - Backend flexibility: Choose Redis or Valkey based on deployment requirements\n26: - Efficient garbage collection: Query sessions by expiry or activity time\n27: - Clean separation: Storage logic isolated from business logic\n28: - Kubernetes integration: Leverages client-go patterns from AR-010\n29: \n30: ---\n31: \n32: ## Scope\n33: \n34: ### In-Scope\n35: \n36: | Deliverable | Description |\n37: |-------------|-------------|\n38: | Store Interface | Define `Store` interface with all CRUD and listing methods |\n39: | Redis Implementation | Implement `redisStore` with Redis client (go-redis/v9) |\n40: | Valkey Implementation | Implement `valkeyStore` with Valkey client (valkey-go) |\n41: | Singleton Access | Provide `Storage()` function with sync.Once initialization |\n42: | Index Maintenance | Maintain ZSET indexes for expiry and last_activity |\n43: | Error Handling | Return `ErrNotFound` for missing sessions |\n44: \n45: ### Code Structure\n46: \n47: ```\n48: pkg/store/\n49: ├── store.go                    # Store interface definition\n50: ├── singleton.go                # Singleton Storage() and initStore()\n51: ├── errors.go                   # ErrNotFound definition\n52: ├── types.go                    # Constants for store types\n53: ├── store_redis.go              # Redis implementation\n54: ├── store_valkey.go             # Valkey implementation\n55: └── (generated test files...)\n56: ```\n57: \n58: ### Configuration\n59: \n60: | Variable | Type | Required | Default | Description |\n61: |----------|------|----------|---------|-------------|\n62: | STORE_TYPE | string | No | \"redis\" | Storage provider (redis/valkey) |\n63: | REDIS_ADDR | string | If redis | - | Redis server address |\n64: | REDIS_PASSWORD | string | If redis* | - | Redis password |\n65: | REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED | string | No | true | Set to \"false\" to allow empty password |\n66: | VALKEY_ADDR | string | If valkey | - | Valkey server addresses (comma-separated) |\n67: | VALKEY_PASSWORD | string | If valkey* | - | Valkey password |\n68: | VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED | string | No | true | Set to \"false\" to allow empty password |\n69: | VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE | string | No | false | Set to \"true\" to disable cache |\n70: | VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE | string | No | false | Set to \"true\" to force single client |\n71: \n72: ### Out-of-Scope\n73: - Session replication across clusters — future enhancement\n74: - Session data encryption at rest — future enhancement\n75: - Connection pooling configuration — future enhancement\n76: - Metrics and observability — future enhancement (AR-013)\n77: \n78: ---\n79: \n80: ## Impact Analysis\n81: \n82: ### Dependencies\n83: \n84: | Dependency | Source | Purpose |\n85: |------------|--------|---------|\n86: | github.com/redis/go-redis/v9 | ^9.x | Redis client |\n87: | github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go | latest | Valkey client |\n88: | github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types | local | SandboxInfo type |\n89: | k8s.io/klog/v2 | ^2.x | Logging (Valkey options) |\n90: \n91: ### Upstream Dependencies\n92: \n93: - **AR-010 Session Management** — Consumes Store for session CRUD\n94: - **AR-009 Router Core** — May use Store for session context\n95: - **pkg/common/types** — Provides `SandboxInfo` struct\n96: \n97: ### Downstream Consumers\n98: \n99: 1. **Session Manager** — Creates, reads, updates, deletes sessions\n100: 2. **Garbage Collector** — Queries expired/inactive sessions for cleanup\n101: 3. **Health Checks** — Uses Ping to verify backend connectivity\n102: \n103: ### Risks\n104: \n105: | Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n106: |------|----------|------------|\n107: | Backend unavailability | High | Health checks, graceful degradation |\n108: | Key conflicts | Medium | Use namespaced key prefixes |\n109: | Data inconsistency | Medium | Use pipeline/multi for atomic operations |\n110: | Password in env | Medium | Require explicit opt-in for empty passwords |\n111: \n112: ---\n113: \n114: ## Alternatives Considered\n115: \n116: ### Option 1: Redis + Valkey via Factory (Selected)\n117: \n118: **Approach**: Single `Store` interface with factory function selecting implementation based on `STORE_TYPE`.\n119: \n120: **Pros**:\n121: - Simple API: callers use `Storage()` without knowing backend\n122: - Easy to add new backends (in-memory, etcd, etc)\n123: - Consistent interface across implementations\n124: - Matches Kubernetes client patterns\n125: \n126: **Cons**:\n127: - Slight runtime dispatch overhead\n128: - More complex testing (mock interface required)\n129: \n130: **Decision**: Selected — provides flexibility and clean abstraction.\n131: \n132: ---\n133: \n134: ### Option 2: Separate Interfaces per Backend\n135: \n136: **Approach**: Define `RedisStore` and `ValkeyStore` interfaces separately.\n137: \n138: **Pros**:\n139: - Type-safe backend selection at compile time\n140: - No runtime dispatch\n141: \n142: **Cons**:\n143: - Duplicated method signatures\n144: - Callers must know backend type\n145: - Difficult to swap backends without code changes\n146: \n147: **Decision**: Rejected — less flexible, harder to maintain.\n148: \n149: ---\n150: \n151: ### Option 3: Generic Key-Value Store\n152: \n153: **Approach**: Use generic KV interface (Get, Set, Delete) and build session logic on top.\n154: \n155: **Pros**:\n156: - More general purpose\n157: - Can reuse for other data\n158: \n159: **Cons**:\n160: - Loses session-specific semantics (expiry index, activity tracking)\n161: - Requires more code in consumers to handle session lifecycle\n162: \n163: **Decision**: Rejected — session-specific operations are core to the use case.\n164: \n165: ---\n166: \n167: ## Implementation Plan\n168: \n169: ### Phase 1: Interface and Types\n170: - [ ] Define `Store` interface with all methods\n171: - [ ] Define `ErrNotFound` error\n172: - [ ] Define store type constants\n173: - [ ] Define `SandboxInfo` and `SandboxEntryPoint` types (or import from pkg/common/types)\n174: \n175: ### Phase 2: Redis Implementation\n176: - [ ] Implement `redisStore` struct\n177: - [ ] Implement `makeRedisOptions` for connection config\n178: - [ ] Implement all Store methods for Redis\n179: - [ ] Use pipeline for atomic multi-command operations\n180: - [ ] Handle ZSET operations for expiry and last_activity indexes\n181: \n182: ### Phase 3: Valkey Implementation\n183: - [ ] Implement `valkeyStore` struct\n184: - [ ] Implement `makeValkeyOptions` for connection config\n185: - [ ] Implement all Store methods for Valkey\n186: - [ ] Use DoMulti for atomic operations\n187: - [ ] Handle optional DisableCache and ForceSingleClient\n188: \n189: ### Phase 4: Singleton and Initialization\n190: - [ ] Implement `Storage()` with sync.Once\n191: - [ ] Implement `initStore()` with provider selection\n192: - [ ] Handle environment variable parsing\n193: - [ ] Add password required validation\n194: - [ ] Log fatal on initialization failure\n195: \n196: ### Phase 5: Testing\n197: - [ ] Unit tests for interface methods\n198: - [ ] Unit tests for key construction\n199: - [ ] Unit tests for error handling (not found, validation)\n200: - [ ] Integration tests with Redis/Valkey (if available)\n201: - [ ] Fake implementations for client testing\n202: \n203: ---\n204: \n205: ## Acceptance Criteria\n206: \n207: - [ ] `Store` interface is defined in `pkg/store`\n208: - [ ] `Storage()` returns initialized store singleton\n209: - [ ] Redis backend implements all Store methods\n210: - [ ] Valkey backend implements all Store methods\n211: - [ ] `STORE_TYPE` selects correct backend\n212: - [ ] Missing session returns `ErrNotFound`\n213: - [ ] Session key uses `session:{id}` format\n214: - [ ] Expiry index maintained in `session:expiry` ZSET\n215: - [ ] Last-activity index maintained in `session:last_activity` ZSET\n216: - [ ] `ListExpiredSandboxes` queries by expiry time\n217: - [ ] `ListInactiveSandboxes` queries by last activity\n218: - [ ] `StoreSandbox` uses atomic pipeline/multi\n219: - [ ] `UpdateSandbox` requires existing key (XX flag)\n220: - [ ] `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` removes from all indexes\n221: - [ ] `UpdateSessionLastActivity` validates key exists\n222: - [ ] Password required unless `*_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`\n223: - [ ] Invalid STORE_TYPE fails initialization\n224: - [ ] Unit tests cover core functionality\n\n(End of file - total 224 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: AR-012 — 会话存储接口定义\n\n## Summary\n\nDefine and implement a `Store` interface in `pkg/store` for persisting sandbox metadata keyed by session ID, with Redis and Valkey backend support. The interface supports session CRUD operations, expiry and last-activity indexing for garbage collection, and provider selection via configuration.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nThe agentcube system requires persistent storage for sandbox metadata associated with user sessions. Currently, there is no standardized interface for session storage, making it difficult to:\n- Support different storage backends (Redis, Valkey)\n- Index sessions for garbage collection (expired/inactive sessions)\n- Maintain session metadata independently of the runtime lifecycle\n\n### Goal\n\nImplement a `Store` interface with:\n- Unified API for session CRUD operations\n- Support for Redis and Valkey backends","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775851191060,"end":1775851191086}}}}
