{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775851216634,"sessionID":"ses_2870582ffffef45IGbHMxX3FsL","part":{"id":"prt_d78fb1ef7001DQV4y1kdo3Uo7t","messageID":"msg_d78fb105c001f1n4hcZpWS64al","sessionID":"ses_2870582ffffef45IGbHMxX3FsL","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775851247127,"sessionID":"ses_2870582ffffef45IGbHMxX3FsL","part":{"id":"prt_d78fb373d001tQpX7NWQ1J20gx","messageID":"msg_d78fb105c001f1n4hcZpWS64al","sessionID":"ses_2870582ffffef45IGbHMxX3FsL","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_be94e72cadd648cd8d70c2c7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# Proposal: AR-013 — Redis 存储实现\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement Redis storage backend for the `Store` interface in `pkg/store`, providing persistent sandbox metadata storage keyed by session ID with expiry and last-activity indexing for garbage collection.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nThe agentcube system requires a Redis-backed storage implementation for session management. The `Store` interface was defined in AR-012; this AR implements the Redis provider using `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9`.\n\n### Goal\n\nImplement `redisStore` in `pkg/store` with:\n- Full `Store` interface implementation\n- Sorted set indexes for expiry and last-activity tracking\n- Pipeline-based atomic operations\n- Configuration via environment variables\n\n### Value\n- Production-ready Redis backend for session storage\n- Efficient session garbage collection via indexed queries\n- Atomic operations ensuring data consistency\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In-Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `store_redis.go` | Redis store implementation |\n| `redisStore` struct | Client, key prefixes, ZSET keys |\n| `makeRedisOptions` | Parse REDIS_ADDR, REDIS_PASSWORD |\n| All Store methods | Ping, GetSandboxBySessionID, StoreSandbox, UpdateSandbox, DeleteSandboxBySessionID, ListExpiredSandboxes, ListInactiveSandboxes, UpdateSessionLastActivity, Close |\n\n### Code Structure\n\n```\npkg/store/\n├── store_redis.go    # Redis implementation\n├── store.go          # Store interface (AR-012)\n├── singleton.go      # Storage() singleton (AR-012)\n├── errors.go         # ErrNotFound (AR-012)\n└── types.go          # Store type constants (AR-012)\n```\n\n### Configuration\n\n| Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n|----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| REDIS_ADDR | Yes | - | Redis server address (host:port) |\n| REDIS_PASSWORD | Yes* | - | Redis password |\n| REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED | No | true | Set to \"false\" to allow empty password |\n| STORE_TYPE | No | redis | Set to \"redis\" for Redis backend |\n\n*Required unless REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false\n\n### Key Patterns\n\n| Key | Pattern | Type |\n|-----|---------|------|\n| Session data | `session:{sessionID}` | String (JSON) |\n| Expiry index | `session:expiry` | ZSET (score = ExpiresAt Unix) |\n| Last-activity index | `session:last_activity` | ZSET (score = activity Unix) |\n\n### Out-of-Scope\n- Valkey implementation (separate AR)\n- Connection pooling configuration\n- Redis Sentinel/Cluster support\n- Data encryption at rest\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Source | Purpose |\n|------------|--------|---------|\n| github.com/redis/go-redis/v9 | ^9.x | Redis client |\n| github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types | local | SandboxInfo type |\n| k8s.io/klog/v2 | ^2.x | Logging |\n\n### Upstream\n\n- **AR-012 Store Interface** — Interface contract to implement\n- **pkg/common/types** — Provides SandboxInfo struct\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n1. **Session Manager** — CRUD operations\n2. **Garbage Collector** — ListExpiredSandboxes, ListInactiveSandboxes\n3. **Health Checks** — Ping for connectivity\n\n### Risks\n\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|------------|\n| Redis unavailable | High | Ping on startup, health checks |\n| Data inconsistency | Medium | Pipeline for atomic operations |\n| Password exposure | Medium | Require explicit opt-in for empty password |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Option 1: Direct Redis Commands (Selected)\n\n**Approach**: Use go-redis/v9 client directly with pipeline for atomic operations.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Mature, well-maintained client\n- Built-in connection pooling\n- Pipeline support for atomic batches\n- Familiar Kubernetes patterns\n\n**Cons**:\n- Additional dependency\n\n**Decision**: Selected — industry standard for Redis in Go.\n\n---\n\n### Option 2: Redis Cluster Mode\n\n**Approach**: Use Redis Cluster for distributed setup.\n\n**Pros**:\n- Horizontal scaling\n- High availability\n\n**Cons**:\n- Key hashing requirements (same slot)\n- More complex deployment\n\n**Decision**: Deferred — single Redis instance meets current scale.\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Struct and Options\n- [ ] Define `redisStore` struct with client, key prefixes\n- [ ] Implement `makeRedisOptions` for env var parsing\n- [ ] Add password validation\n\n### Phase 2: Core Operations\n- [ ] Implement `Ping` — PING → expect PONG\n- [ ] Implement `GetSandboxBySessionID` — GET session:{id}\n- [ ] Implement `StoreSandbox` — Pipeline: SETNX, ZADD expiry, ZADD last_activity\n- [ ] Implement `UpdateSandbox` — SET key value XX\n\n### Phase 3: Deletion and Updates\n- [ ] Implement `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` — Pipeline: DEL, ZREM both indexes\n- [ ] Implement `UpdateSessionLastActivity` — GET verify exists, ZADD\n\n### Phase 4: Listing\n- [ ] Implement `ListExpiredSandboxes` — ZRANGEBYSCORE on expiry, then GET\n- [ ] Implement `ListInactiveSandboxes` — ZRANGEBYSCORE on last_activity, then GET\n- [ ] Handle orphan ZSET entries gracefully\n\n### Phase 5: Lifecycle\n- [ ] Implement `Close` — cli.Close()\n\n### Phase 6: Testing\n- [ ] Unit tests for each method\n- [ ] Test key construction\n- [ ] Test error cases (not found, nil input, validation)\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `redisStore` implements full `Store` interface\n- [ ] `REDIS_ADDR` and `REDIS_PASSWORD` correctly configure client\n- [ ] Password required unless REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false\n- [ ] Session key format: `session:{id}`\n- [ ] Expiry index: ZSET with score = ExpiresAt.Unix()\n- [ ] Last-activity index: ZSET with score = time.Now().Unix() on store\n- [ ] StoreSandbox uses atomic pipeline\n- [ ] UpdateSandbox requires existing key (XX flag)\n- [ ] DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes from all indexes\n- [ ] ListExpiredSandboxes queries by expiry time\n- [ ] ListInactiveSandboxes queries by last activity\n- [ ] Missing session returns ErrNotFound\n- [ ] Nil sandbox rejected with error\n- [ ] Empty session ID rejected on UpdateSessionLastActivity\n- [ ] Close properly terminates connection","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775851247089,"end":1775851247124}}}}
